ry":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"components":[],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"customfield_13000":null,"description":"The fix to EUCA-7269 includes a new configurable property:\r\ncloud.images.maximagesizegb\r\n\r\nThe unit is GBs. The default value for a new installation is 30. Meaning that the largest image that a user (or admin) can register is 30GB.\r\n\r\nExample output:\r\n{code}\r\n[root@a-01 eee]# euca-register images/windows7_pro_x64.kvm.img.manifest.xml -n windowsimage_2\r\neuca-register: error (RegisterImageType): Cannot register image of size 15728640000 bytes because it exceeds the configured maximum instance-store image size of 10 GB. Please contact your administrator \r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThe cloud administrator can modify this limit using:\r\n{code}\r\neuca-modify-property -p cloud.images.maximagesizegb=<max size in gigabytes>\r\n{code}\r\nThe value must be an integer, any value <= 0 disables the size check and means that there is no limit on the size of images that may be registered by users.\r\n\r\nChanging the value will *not* invalidate previously registered images.\r\n\r\nThe maximum image size in EC2 is 10GB, so cloud admins that want to be exactly the same as EC2 should manually configure this property to a value of 10. We have set it at 30GB because that is the default Walrus Image Cache size and it allows use of Windows 2008+ images that are not allowed with a maximum size of 10GB.\r\n\r\nFor upgraded installations, the maximum size is set to '0' if the previous version of Eucalyptus did not include this property (pre-3.4.0) so the admin must explicitly set a limit if one is desired.\r\n","customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"attachment":[],"summary":"New configurable 